				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What types of armor would you choose to equip?<a name="26986"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 11 04 12:07 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Lambent was the mid-range armor for bards, meaning it was intended for bards in their 30s back when it was introduced.  These days, lambent is considered subpar at nearly all levels because of the significantly better options that are currently available.  
<br />

<br />
You can often find tailored and smithed acrylia armor, spider fur drops from Velks, and many other very cheap options that are significant upgrades over lambent.  (Actually, I'm the worst person to tell you what's good bard twink gear these days so someone else chime in here with suggestions?)
<br />

<br />
When I was level 23 (which was lots of years ago), my lambent pants were my pride and joy, a status symbol and definitely high-end.  But then blackened alloy from Runnyeye was hip then too.  The bottom line is that lambent has been surpassed by the far better gear that has been introduced with each new expansion.
<br />

<br />
However, and this is purely my opinion, if you can be an effective bard in crap gear, you'll be a remarkable bard in decent gear.  Just tell people you're retro.
<br />

<br />
Calli</span></td>
