				<td colspan="2"><span>with mainly lambent you are in a bad situation if you plan on tanking since as mentioned it was intended for low/mid level range back when the max level was 50 and the worst raid mobs in the game hit for maybe around 500.  Now with PoP/GoD those are normal hits from trash mobs, so you are way over your head.   But as a bard (like i enjoy telling other melee at raids) you dont have to tank or melee :P.  
<br />

<br />
If you dont care about faction, ask a group to go kill with you in skyshrine, the guardian/sentry armor there is better than lambent.  So would be going to hate and trying for old world planar armor.  PoG would be another option even if you could only field a single group of 55 to 65 players.  Similar armor if killing in Kael for thugadin quest armor.  A single group should also by now (within reason/level) be able to kill in ToV for quest armor drops.
<br />

<br />
If you have money, buy ornate armor or tradeskill armor.  
<br />

<br />
There are other random zone drops on a piece by piece basis that would be improvements.  </span></td>
